  <dashboards>
    <dashboard name='Age_BMI_Diabetics_Story' type='storyboard'>
      <style>
        <style-rule element='story-point-caption'>
          <format attr='width' value='981' />
        </style-rule>
      </style>
      <size maxheight='964' maxwidth='1016' minheight='964' minwidth='1016' />
      <zones>
        <zone h='100000' id='2' type-v2='layout-basic' w='100000' x='0' y='0'>
          <zone h='98340' id='1' param='vert' removable='false' type-v2='layout-flow' w='98426' x='787' y='830'>
            <zone h='3423' id='3' type-v2='title' w='98426' x='787' y='830' />
            <zone h='10477' id='4' is-fixed='true' paired-zone-id='5' removable='false' type-v2='flipboard-nav' w='98426' x='787' y='4253' />
            <zone h='84440' id='5' paired-zone-id='4' removable='false' type-v2='flipboard' w='98426' x='787' y='14730'>
              <flipboard active-id='1' nav-type='caption' show-nav-arrows='true'>
                <story-points>
                  <story-point caption='Objective&#10;&#10;This visualization explores how Age Category, Diabetic Status, and Average Body Mass Index (BMI) are related. The treemap helps identify which age groups and diabetes categories have higher average BMI values.&#10;&#10;Insights&#10;The treemap shows that BMI varies across different age groups and diabetic conditions, indicating that body weight patterns are not uniform throughout the population.&#10;Several young and middle-aged groups (18–24, 25–29, 30–34, and 45–49) display relatively darker shades, suggesting higher average BMI values in these categories.&#10;Individuals diagnosed with diabetes (&quot;Yes&quot;) or borderline diabetes generally appear in darker-colored blocks than those without diabetes, indicating a tendency toward higher average BMI.&#10;Older age groups such as 70–74, 75–79, and 80 or older are also represented, showing that elevated BMI is present across multiple age ranges rather than being limited to one stage of life.&#10;The tooltip (for example, 18–24, Yes (during pregnancy), Avg. BMI = 30.67) demonstrates that some subgroups have BMI values in the obese range, highlighting potential health concerns.&#10;Key Finding&#10;&#10;The analysis suggests that higher BMI is observed across several age groups, particularly among individuals with diabetes or borderline diabetes. This indicates a strong relationship between body weight and diabetes status, emphasizing the importance of maintaining a healthy BMI to reduce health risks.&#10;&#10;Healthcare Insight&#10;&#10;Healthcare organizations can use this analysis to:&#10;&#10;Identify age groups with higher average BMI for targeted wellness programs.&#10;Promote healthy eating, regular exercise, and weight management among individuals at risk of diabetes.&#10;Prioritize preventive screening for populations with elevated BMI to reduce the likelihood of diabetes-related complications.' captured-sheet='Age vs BMI vs Diabetics' id='1' />
                </story-points>
              </flipboard>
            </zone>
          </zone>
          <zone-style>
            <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
            <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
            <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
            <format attr='margin' value='8' />
          </zone-style>
        </zone>
      </zones>
      <simple-id uuid='{612AEC0E-47D8-4C5B-B56B-A92B7E8817BE}' />
    </dashboard>
    <dashboard name='Dashboard_Story' type='storyboard'>
      <style>
        <style-rule element='story-point-caption'>
          <format attr='width' value='957' />
        </style-rule>
      </style>
      <size maxheight='964' maxwidth='1016' minheight='964' minwidth='1016' />
      <zones>
        <zone h='100000' id='2' type-v2='layout-basic' w='100000' x='0' y='0'>
          <zone h='98340' id='1' param='vert' removable='false' type-v2='layout-flow' w='98426' x='787' y='830'>
            <zone h='3423' id='3' type-v2='title' w='98426' x='787' y='830' />
            <zone h='10477' id='4' is-fixed='true' paired-zone-id='5' removable='false' type-v2='flipboard-nav' w='98426' x='787' y='4253' />
            <zone h='84440' id='5' paired-zone-id='4' removable='false' type-v2='flipboard' w='98426' x='787' y='14730'>
              <flipboard active-id='1' nav-type='caption' show-nav-arrows='true'>
                <story-points>
                  <story-point caption='&quot;Heart disease affects individuals across every general health category. The highest number of recorded cases appears among people reporting &apos;Good&apos; health, followed by those with &apos;Fair&apos; health. This indicates that self-perceived good health does not eliminate the risk of heart disease, emphasizing the importance of routine cardiovascular screening and preventive healthcare.&quot;' captured-sheet='Heart Disease Analysis Dashboard' id='1' />
                </story-points>
              </flipboard>
            </zone>
          </zone>
          <zone-style>
            <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
            <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
            <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
            <format attr='margin' value='8' />
          </zone-style>
        </zone>
      </zones>
      <simple-id uuid='{33317982-D40D-40BF-A5E6-354694B205C6}' />
    </dashboard>
    <dashboard name='General Health_story' type='storyboard'>
      <style>
        <style-rule element='story-point-caption'>
          <format attr='width' value='942' />
        </style-rule>
      </style>
      <size maxheight='964' maxwidth='1016' minheight='964' minwidth='1016' />
      <zones>
        <zone h='100000' id='2' type-v2='layout-basic' w='100000' x='0' y='0'>
          <zone h='98340' id='7' param='vert' removable='false' type-v2='layout-flow' w='98426' x='787' y='830'>
            <zone h='98340' id='1' param='vert' removable='false' type-v2='layout-flow' w='98426' x='787' y='830'>
              <zone h='10477' id='4' is-fixed='true' paired-zone-id='5' removable='false' type-v2='flipboard-nav' w='98426' x='787' y='830' />
              <zone h='87863' id='5' paired-zone-id='4' removable='false' type-v2='flipboard' w='98426' x='787' y='11307'>
                <flipboard active-id='4' nav-type='caption' show-nav-arrows='true'>
                  <story-points>
                    <story-point caption='Objective:&#10;This visualization analyzes the relationship between self-reported general health status and the number of individuals diagnosed with heart disease.&#10;&#10;Insights:&#10;&#10;The largest bubble represents individuals with Good general health, indicating that this group has the highest number of heart disease cases in the filtered dataset.&#10;The Fair health category also shows a significant number of heart disease cases, making it the second-largest group.&#10;Individuals reporting Poor health have fewer cases than the Good and Fair categories, but still represent a notable portion of the affected population.&#10;The Very Good health category has a relatively smaller number of heart disease cases.&#10;The smallest bubble corresponds to the Excellent health category, suggesting that heart disease is least common among people who perceive their health as excellent.&#10;&#10;Key Finding:&#10;Heart disease is observed across all health categories. Although people reporting Good health contribute the highest number of cases, this may reflect that more individuals in the dataset fall into this category. Better perceived health is generally associated with fewer heart disease cases, while Fair and Poor health categories continue to show a substantial burden.&#10;&#10;Business/Healthcare Insight:&#10;Healthcare providers should not focus only on individuals who report poor health. Preventive screenings and awareness programs should also target people who consider themselves in good health, as heart disease can still occur in this population. Promoting healthy lifestyles and regular medical checkups may help detect cardiovascular risks earlier.' captured-sheet='General Health vs Heart disease' id='4' />
                  </story-points>
                </flipboard>
              </zone>
            </zone>
          </zone>
          <zone-style>
            <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
            <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
            <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
            <format attr='margin' value='8' />
          </zone-style>
        </zone>
      </zones>
      <simple-id uuid='{362159E5-EA73-47A9-A071-05F53E5B67AD}' />
    </dashboard>
